quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  5,20,"And when Moses said to his people, \"O my people! Remember Allah's Favour upon you when He raised Prophets among you and made you kings and gave you what He had not given to any of the worlds.\"h"
  5,21,"O my people! Enter the holy land which Allah has assigned to you, and turn not on your backs; for, then, you will turn back doomed"
  5,22,"They said, \"O Moses! In it indeed live a cruel people. And we shall definitely not enter it until they go out from it. And if they go out from it, then indeed we shall enter"
  5,23,"Two men of those who feared and upon both of whom Allah had bestowed favour, said, \"Enter upon them by the gate, and when you enter it, you shall indeed be victorious. And upon Allah put your trust, if you do believe"
  5,24,"They said, \"O Moses! We shall never enter it so long as they are in it. Go then, you and your Lord, and fight you both with them. We shall indeed sit right here"
  5,25,"He [Moses] said, \"My Lord! I have indeed no control but on my own self and on my brother. Make a distinction, then, between us and the transgressing people"
  5,26,"Allah said, \"So it is forbidden to them for forty years, during which time they shall suffer, wandering from place to place on the earth. Be not sad then for the transgressing people"